-- Japanese Bought Net 875.4 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   I s a a c   A q u i n o
-- 2012-09-05T23:51:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-05/japanese-bought-net-875-4-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended Aug. 31 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 875.4 billion yen ($11.2 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 34.6 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 70.2 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 911 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 395.4 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 44.8 billion yen in stocks, and bought 799.3 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 1149.9
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
Isaac Aquino in Tokyo at   iaquino1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
